  "intent_precise": "111210-part-5.ot2.apiv2: Using temp_plate (plate, slot 5), samples_plate (pcr_plate, slot 2), pcr_plate_deck (pcr_plate, slot 5). With thermocycler module, temperature module. (1) Pause: Place End repair / dA tailing sample plate in Slot 2\n                and a new PCR plate in Slot 5 (2) Set temperature to 20\u00b0C. (3) Open thermocycler lid. (4) Adjust temperature. (5) Pause: Place adaptors and ligation master mix tubes\n                on the temperature module. (6) Transfer 5\u00b5L from source to destination. (7) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Transfer 45\u00b5L from source to destination. (9) Mix 7 times at 25\u00b5L. (10) Pause: Please centrifuge the PCR plate in slot 2 and keep on ice\n                or the temperature module while thermocycler reaches 20C. (11) Pause: Please place plate in thermocycler to begin incubation. (12) Close thermocycler lid. (13) Set temperature to 20\u00b0C. (14) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (15) Open thermocycler lid. (16) Pause: Protocol complete. Proceed to adapter ligation cleanup.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform temperature control (4\u00b0C, 20\u00b0C), thermocycling. (volumes 5\u00b5L-50\u00b5L)",
  "intent": "For this adapter ligation protocol, start by placing your end repair/dA tailing sample plate in slot 2 and a fresh PCR plate in slot 5, then set the temperature module to 20\u00b0C and open the thermocycler lid. Once everything's at temperature, place your adaptors and ligation master mix tubes on the temperature module, then transfer 5\u00b5L, 50\u00b5L, and 45\u00b5L from source to destination wells respectively, mixing 7 times at 25\u00b5L volume. After mixing, centrifuge the PCR plate from slot 2 and keep it on ice or the temperature module while the thermocycler reaches 20\u00b0C, then place the plate in the thermocycler, close the lid, and run the incubation at 20\u00b0C followed by cooling to 4\u00b0C. Once the thermocycler finishes and you open the lid, you're ready to proceed to adapter ligation cleanup.",
